                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#63v">f. 63v</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#63v">63v</locus>: ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘዕቁባ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ዘወሀበ [sic]፡
                              ለዮሐንስ፡ ዘተሣየጣ፡ በወርቁ፡ ጸሎቱ፡ ወበረከቱ፡ ይዕቀቦሙ፡ ለአቡሁ፡ ወለእሙ፡ ተስፋ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ወለተ፡
                              ማርያም፡ ወለገብሩ፡ ዕቁባ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#63v">63v</locus>: This is a book of ʿƎquba Śǝllāse who
                              has donated it to (the church of) John (the Baptist), who bought it
                              for his own money. May [God’s] protection and blessing guard his
                              father and his mother, Tasfā Giyorgis [and] Walatta Māryām, and His
                              servant ʿƎquba Śǝllāse for ever and ever. Amen.</quote>
                           <note> </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#148va">ff. 148va-149</locus>
                           <desc>r: 1 Cor. 11:23-29.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> Crudely written. Parts of the same text, in the
                           same hand, are repeated in <locus target="#150v">150v</locus>
                           <note>. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#149v">f. 149v</locus>
                           <desc>: Ownership note (?).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Crudely written, part of the text poorly visible. The name of John
                              the Baptist (patron saint of the church) can be discerned. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#150v">f. 150v</locus>
                           <desc>: Ownership note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#150v">150v</locus>: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ የደብረ [sic]፡ ዮሐንስ፡ መጥምቅ፡
                              ወሠማዕት። ዘፈሐቃ፡ ወዘሰረቃ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#150v">150v</locus>: This is a book of the church of
                              John the Baptist and Martyr. He who erases [its text] and he who
                              steals it shall be excommunicated by the authority of Peter and
                              Paul.</quote>
                           <note> The beginning of a pen trial is adjoined to the end of note.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Round stamp is visible in the bottom right corner (the
                           inner part of the stamp did not leave the imprint): <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>.
 - In the upper margin, notes marking beginning of
                           important texts: <locus target="#28r">28r</locus>, 33r, 34r, 38v.
 -
                           A small piece of parchment from a different Ms. has been sewn on to the
                           folio, with a text fragment (prayer?) visible: <locus target="#31v">31v</locus>.
 - <locus target="#49r">49r</locus>, 50r, etc. (in
                           the upper margin): ወደ crudely written above the text.
 - <locus target="#63">63</locus> has been cut short, only about half of the
                           folio is preserved.
 - Crude notes: <locus target="#64r">64r</locus>,
                           69v (in the upper margin).
 - Crude note (pen trial?), with simple
                           ornament beneath: <locus target="#144v">144v</locus> (in the upper
                           margin).
 - Repetition of Additio 1, executed by the same hand (?):
                              <locus target="#150v">150v</locus>.
 - Notes (writing exercise?):
                              <locus target="#151v">151v</locus>.
 - Traces of crude notes
                           visible: <locus target="#152v">152v</locus>.</item>
                     </list>
