               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0129DMD">Dǝblā Yoḥannǝs Maṭmǝq</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1770" notAfter="1796">Yosef is mentioned as the Patriarch
                           (<locus target="#69vb">69vb</locus>), and Yosab is mentioned as the
                        Metropolitan (<locus target="#69vb">69vb</locus>, 70rb). Yosab (II) was
                        Metropolitan of Ethiopia from ca. 1770 to 1803; Joseph was the lay name of
                        John XVIII, Patriarch of Alexandria in 1769-96.</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>ʿƎquba Śǝllāse (s. Additio 1 and supplication
                     formulas within the main text). The donation note also mentions the names of
                     the donor's parents, Tasfā Giyorgis and Walatta Māryām.</provenance></history>
